      "endCol": 0
    },
    {
      "text": "- Goal: `embed.MockModel` implements `ContextualEmbeddingModel` (deterministic, but sibling-dependent so contextual output differs from isolated for the same chunk); `config.ModelConfig` gains `contextualizeText` with TOML tag, wired through `Default()`/`Load()` merge. No manager behavior change yet (field read but unused).\n- Verification:\n  - Behavior: config round-trips the new key and defaults to false.\n    - Setup: write a `pkb.toml` with `[embedding] contextualizeText = true`; also load with no file.\n    - Actions: `config.Load(root)`.\n    - Expected outcome: field true when set, false by default; existing fields unaffected.\n  - Behavior: mock EmbedDocument auto-chunks a document and returns chunk+vector pairs.\n    - Setup: MockModel with a deterministic splitter (e.g. split on blank lines) producing N chunks.\n    - Actions: EmbedDocument a multi-paragraph document.\n    - Expected outcome: N `ContextualChunk`s whose texts reconstruct the input and whose vectors are deterministic per chunk text.\n- Before moving on: confirm tests, vet, build, lint pass.",
      "contextualizedText": "- Goal: `embed.MockModel` implements `ContextualEmbeddingModel` (deterministic, but sibling-dependent so contextual output differs from isolated for the same chunk); `config.ModelConfig` gains `contextualizeText` with TOML tag, wired through `Default()`/`Load()` merge. No manager behavior change yet (field read but unused).\n- Verification:\n  - Behavior: config round-trips the new key and defaults to false.\n    - Setup: write a `pkb.toml` with `[embedding] contextualizeText = true`; also load with no file.\n    - Actions: `config.Load(root)`.\n    - Expected outcome: field true when set, false by default; existing fields unaffected.\n  - Behavior: mock EmbedDocument auto-chunks a document and returns chunk+vector pairs.\n    - Setup: MockModel with a deterministic splitter (e.g. split on blank lines) producing N chunks.\n    - Actions: EmbedDocument a multi-paragraph document.\n    - Expected outcome: N `ContextualChunk`s whose texts reconstruct the input and whose vectors are deterministic per chunk text.\n- Before moving on: confirm tests, vet, build, lint pass.",
      "headingContext": "",
